# Memory Map Metadata Guide

Each location on the memory map should include enough information to help future users understand where the memory comes from and how it may be used.

## Recommended fields

- `id`: Unique location ID, e.g. `PB-LOC-001`
- `title`: Public-facing name of the place
- `latitude`: Approximate latitude
- `longitude`: Approximate longitude
- `description`: Short description of the place or memory
- `themes`: Main themes connected to the place
- `source`: Oral history, community memory, photograph, family archive, publication, etc.
- `related_interview_id`: Oral history reference, if any
- `public_use`: Yes, No, or Limited
- `sensitivity`: Public, community review needed, restricted, sacred/private
- `media`: Photo, audio, video, document, or object reference
- `contributor_credit`: Name, initials, family name, anonymous, or restricted
- `date_added`: Date added to the map
- `review_status`: Pending, reviewed, approved, restricted

## Important note

Locations may be approximate.

For sensitive places, such as burial sites, sacred locations, private family homes, or spiritually significant areas, avoid publishing exact coordinates unless the community has clearly agreed.
